325|      "title": "How to Book Driving License Slot in Bhopal – RTO Appointment Guide 2026",
326|      "category": "driving-license",
327|      "description": "Complete guide to book DL slot at Bhopal RTO. Online appointment for learner's license and driving license test at MP RTO offices.",
328|      "date": "2026-06-09",
329|      "readTime": "6 min",
330|      "content": [
331|        {
332|          "type": "p",
333|          "text": "Booking a driving license slot at Bhopal RTO doesn't have to be confusing. Whether you're applying for a Learner's License (LLR) or the permanent Driving License (DL), here is the exact process for 2026."
334|        },
335|        {
336|          "type": "h2",
337|          "text": "Bhopal RTO Offices"
338|        },
339|        {
340|          "type": "p",
341|          "text": "Bhopal has two main RTO offices where you can book slots:"
342|        },
343|        {
344|          "type": "table",
345|          "headers": [
346|            "Office",
347|            "Location",
348|            "Jurisdiction"
349|          ],
350|          "rows": [
351|            [
352|              "RTO Bhopal (RTO-47)",
353|              "Govindpura, Near TT Nagar",
354|              "Bhopal city & rural areas"
355|            ],
356|            [
357|              "ARTO Bhopal",
358|              "Habibganj",
359|              "Some Bhopal zones"
360|            ]
361|          ]
362|        },
363|        {
364|          "type": "h2",
365|          "text": "Step 1: Visit the MP Parivahan Website"
366|        },
367|        {
368|          "type": "step",
369|          "title": "Go to MP Parivahan Portal",
370|          "text": "Open https://parivahan.mpg.gov.in or https://sarathi.parivahan.gov.in. The Sarathi portal is the central system used across India."
371|        },
372|        {
373|          "type": "step",
374|          "title": "Select Madhya Pradesh & Bhopal",
375|          "text": "Choose Madhya Pradesh as the state and then select Bhopal (RTO-47 or the relevant RTO office) as your RTO."
376|        },
377|        {
378|          "type": "h2",
379|          "text": "Step 2: Choose Service Type"
380|        },
381|        {
382|          "type": "p",
383|          "text": "You'll see different options. Select what you need:"
384|        },
385|        {
386|          "type": "ul",
387|          "items": [
388|            "New Learner's License (LLR) — First-time applicant for a learning license",
389|            "New Driving License (DL) — After completing your learner's license period (minimum 30 days for non-transport, 60 days for transport)",
390|            "Renewal — If your DL has expired",
391|            "Duplicate DL — If your license is lost or damaged"
392|          ]
393|        },
394|        {
395|          "type": "h2",
396|          "text": "Step 3: Fill Application Form"
397|        },
398|        {
399|          "type": "p",
400|          "text": "Fill in your personal details: name, date of birth, address, and Aadhaar number. You can save your application number for future reference — note it down."
401|        },
402|        {
403|          "type": "h2",
404|          "text": "Step 4: Book Your Slot"
405|        },
406|        {
407|          "type": "step",
408|          "title": "Select Date and Time",
409|          "text": "The portal shows available dates and time slots for your chosen RTO. Morning slots (10 AM - 1 PM) are usually available. Pick a time that works for you."
410|        },
411|        {
412|          "type": "step",
413|          "title": "Pay the Fee Online",
414|          "text": "Fees can be paid via debit card, credit card, net banking, or UPI. The fee structure (approximate):"
415|        },
416|        {
417|          "type": "table",
418|          "headers": [
419|            "Service",
420|            "Fee (approx)"
421|          ],
422|          "rows": [
423|            [
424|              "Learner's License (LLR)",
425|              "₹150 + test fee"
426|            ],
427|            [
428|              "Driving License (DL) Non-Transport",
429|              "₹200 + test fee"
430|            ],
431|            [
432|              "DL Transport",
433|              "₹300 + test fee"
434|            ],
435|            [
436|              "Renewal (after 5 years)",
437|              "₹200"
438|            ]
439|          ]
440|        },
441|        {
442|          "type": "step",
443|          "title": "Get Confirmation",
444|          "text": "After payment, you'll receive a confirmation SMS and email with your slot details. Save this — you'll need it at the RTO."
445|        },
446|        {
447|          "type": "h2",
448|          "text": ""
449|        },
450|        {
451|          "type": "tip",
452|          "text": "Slots at Bhopal RTO fill up fast, especially at the start of the month. Book at least 1-2 weeks in advance during peak seasons (April-June and November-December when students apply)."
453|        },
454|        {
455|          "type": "h2",
456|          "text": "What to Bring to the RTO"
457|        },
458|        {
459|          "type": "ul",
460|          "items": [
461|            "Printed application form (from Sarathi portal)",
462|            "Original Aadhaar card + photocopy",
463|            "Address proof (electricity bill, bank statement, etc.)",
464|            "Passport-size photographs (4-6 copies)",
465|            "Medical certificate (Form 1-A) from a registered doctor",
466|            "Fee payment receipt (online payment proof)",
467|            "For DL test: your own vehicle (two-wheeler or car) + helmet"
468|          ]
469|        },
470|        {
471|          "type": "h2",
472|          "text": "Frequently Asked Questions"
473|        },
474|        {
475|          "type": "h3",
476|          "text": "Can I book a DL slot without going online?"
477|        },
478|        {
479|          "type": "p",
480|          "text": "No, slot booking is fully online through the Sarathi portal. However, you can visit the RTO help desk and they can assist you with the online booking."
481|        },
482|        {
483|          "type": "h3",
484|          "text": "What if I miss my slot?"
485|        },
486|        {
487|          "type": "p",
488|          "text": "If you miss your appointment, you'll need to book a new slot. The previous fee is generally not refundable. Always reach the RTO at least 30 minutes before your slot time."
489|        }
490|      ]
